properties.NAME: Afghanistan
properties.summary: OTI increases resilience in areas vulnerable to insurgent exploitation by strengthening ties between local actors, customary governance structures, and the national government.

properties.NAME: Côte d'Ivoire
properties.summary: To mitigate serious political, social, and security challenges emerging from 2011 post-election violence and civil war, OTI’s program improves public confidence in the post-conflict recovery process through enhanced governance and effective community initiatives.

properties.NAME: Honduras
properties.summary: In the world’s deadliest country, OTI supports civil society engagement and community revitalization to reduce violence.

properties.NAME: Lebanon
properties.summary: OTI strengthens social cohesion through quick impact programming to mitigate tensions between Lebanon host communities and Syrian refugees.

properties.NAME: Libya
properties.summary: In post-Qadhafi Libya, OTI amplifies citizens’ voices and increases participation in new democratic processes.

properties.NAME: Mali
properties.summary: Following the expulsion of extremist groups from northern Mali in 2013, OTI supports broad-based, community-driven reconciliation efforts as well as activities aimed at increasing citizen confidence in the democratic process.

properties.NAME: Myanmar
properties.FORMAL_EN: Republic of the Union of Myanmar
properties.summary: In response to significant political reforms, OTI addresses urgent transition needs and fosters greater participation in peace and reform processes through support to civil society and other key stakeholders.

properties.NAME: Pakistan
properties.summary: OTI supports stability and development programs in conflict-prone communities throughout volatile areas in Pakistan.

properties.NAME: Syria
properties.summary: In response to the ongoing conflict, OTI supports Syrian efforts to mitigate suffering, rehabilitate service delivery, and enable an inclusive, peaceful, and participatory political transition.

properties.NAME: Tunisia
properties.summary: In the aftermath of the January 2011 fall of Tunisian President Ben Ali, OTI supports citizen engagement in the political transition and encourages equitable, responsive, and legitimate governance.

properties.NAME: Yemen
properties.summary: OTI supports government and civil society actors to engage in an inclusive and peaceful political transition through targeted assistance in key rural and urban areas.
